Linear Stage

Linear Stage block models the mechanism that converts rotary motion of motor to linear motion in a Cartesian robot. The linear stage is a rigid body that consists of a linear guide (fixed) and a carriage (moving). You can use the Prismatic Joint block to connect the linear guide and the carriage. These figures show a linear stage with Rail-block and Lead screw-bearing configurations respectively.

Ports

B - Base Frame

Body frame located at the centroid of the bottom surface of the fixed linear guide. Use this frame to connect a linear stage to other components, like mounts, columns or other linear stages.

F - Follower Frame

Body frame located at the centroid of the top surface of the moving carriage. Use this frame to connect a linear stage to other components, like mounts, or other linear stages.

JB - Joint Base Frame

Body frame located at the centroid of the mating surface of the fixed linear guide (top surface of a rail or curved surface of a cylindrical lead screw). Use this frame to connect to a Prismatic Joint.

JF - Joint Follower Frame

Body frame located at the centroid of the mating surface of the moving carriage (inner flat surface of a block or annular surface of a bearing). Use this frame to connect to a Prismatic Joint.

Parameters

Configuration

Guide system

The configuration of the guide system, specified as Rail-block and Lead screw-bearing. The type of linear guide is a rail and the type of carriage is a block for Rail-block guide system. The type of linear guide is a lead screw and the type of carriage is a bearing for Lead screw-bearing guide system. The drive mechanism of the guide system is not modeled. These figures show a linear stage with Rail-block and Lead screw-bearing configurations respectively.

Guide axis

The axis direction of the linear stage, or the direction of motion of carriage of the linear stage. You can set the Guide axis either to X-axis, Y-axis or Z-axis.
If you set the Guide axis to X-axis, the linear stage is oriented in the X-axis direction of the world frame.
If you set the Guide axis to Y-axis, the linear stage is oriented in the Y-axis direction of the world frame.
If you set the Guide axis to Z-axis, the linear stage is oriented in the Z-axis direction of the world frame.

Inertia (Linear Guide)

Inertia type

Inertia type, specified as Custom or Calculate from Geometry. Select Custom to model a distributed mass with the specified moments and products of inertia. Select Calculate from Geometry to enable the block to automatically calculate the rotational inertia properties from the solid geometry and specified mass density of the linear guide.

Density

Material density of the linear guide, specified as a positive scalar. The unit is kg/m^3.

Mass

Total mass of the linear guide, specified as a positive scalar. The unit is kg. Mass is distributed to the rail (or leadscrew) only and the mass of the motor housing and the tail end plate is assumed to be zero.

Center of mass

[x y z] coordinates of the center of mass of the linear guide relative to the body frame located at the Base Frame of linear stage.

Moments of inertia

Three-element vector with the [Ixx Iyy Izz] moments of inertia specified relative to a frame with origin at the center of mass and axes parallel to the body frame located at the Base Frame of linear stage. The moments of inertia are the diagonal elements of the inertia tensor
where,

Products of inertia

Three-element vector with the [Iyz Izx Ixy] products of inertia specified relative to a frame with origin at the center of mass and axes parallel to the body frame located at the Base Frame of linear stage. The products of inertia are the off-diagonal elements of the inertia tensor
where,

Inertia (Carriage)

Inertia type

Inertia type, specified as Custom or Calculate from Geometry. Select Custom to model a distributed mass with the specified moments and products of inertia. Select Calculate from Geometry to enable the block to automatically calculate the rotational inertia properties from the solid geometry and specified mass density of the carriage.

Density

Material density of the carriage, specified as a positive scalar. The unit is kg/m^3.

Mass

Total mass of the carriage, specified as a positive scalar. The unit is kg.

Center of mass

[x y z] coordinates of the center of mass of the carriage relative to the body frame located at the Base Frame of linear stage.

Moments of inertia

Three-element vector with the [Ixx Iyy Izz] moments of inertia specified relative to a frame with origin at the center of mass and axes parallel to the body frame located at the Base Frame of linear stage. The moments of inertia are the diagonal elements of the inertia tensor
where,

Products of inertia

Three-element vector with the [Iyz Izx Ixy] products of inertia specified relative to a frame with origin at the center of mass and axes parallel to the body frame located at the Base Frame of linear stage. The products of inertia are the off-diagonal elements of the inertia tensor
where,

Graphic

Linear guide color

Color of the rail (or leadscrew) graphic under direct white light, specified as an [R G B] or [R G B A] vector on a 0–1 scale. An optional fourth element (A) specifies the color opacity on a scale of 0–1. Omitting the opacity element is equivalent to specifying a value of 1.

Carriage color

Color of the carriage graphic under direct white light, specified as an [R G B] or [R G B A] vector on a 0–1 scale. An optional fourth element (A) specifies the color opacity on a scale of 0–1. Omitting the opacity element is equivalent to specifying a value of 1.
